      "text": "We’ve come to understand at Griffin that The Intellectual Classroom Environment is primarily about thinking with the central educator understanding being, thinking or changes in thinking equals learning. With this mindset, passive types of ‘learning’ where learners remember, replicate or reiterate aren’t viewed as genuinely developing understanding. Maybe short-term knowledge, but unlikely deep long-lasting understanding."
